This is Home Frite's first physical outpost, and it's seriously delicious. Their eponymous frites are thick-cut and crispy, with several sauce options to suit your taste. I would probably enjoy a more traditional side of mayo with them, but the lemon aioli is a decent substitute, and you can't beat the range or variety.  Their sandwiches are also top notch; beautifully made and flavored perfectly. I personally recommend the lamb sausage sandwich, which is stuffed with warm frites, green onions, and grated parm. Instant classic; perfect for a quick, tasty lunch or late-night meal.  Home Frite's ambiance is clean and inviting; bar-style seating or individual tables are available, and the brick-walled interior is comfortably simple. Beer and other alcoholic beverages are served, and prices are very reasonable, with special lunch offers. Make every effort to try out this new spot when you're in Bed-Stuy!
Really recommend! Loved the fast and friendly service, and enjoyed the most iconic pommes frites in NYC in the hip BedStuy neighborhood
